{
  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Sanjay Colaro versus State of Karnataka pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_4_2558_2562','2025INSC686'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SANJAY COLARO<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF KARNATAKA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2558</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 686</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007122025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : VIKRAM NATH, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Matter pertains to the extension of benefit under the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 to the appellant for causing a road accident, resulting in the death of the pedestrian. Headnotes&dagger; Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 &ndash; Benefit under &ndash; Death by rash by the appellant resulting in the death of the pedestrian &ndash; Trial court convicted the appellant u/ss.279 and 304A with six months imprisonment and fine &ndash; High Court upheld the conviction and sentence awarded to the appellant &ndash; Interference with: Held: Not called for &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2133/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_4_2558_2562','2025INSC686','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_4_2558_2562','2025INSC686','H